<subSubSection id="7027775DC84BA236324CBAEA05851AF3" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="0B57DD3152C2B3AF67C86B29B00D3CDF" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A68A68DE2A8D03ECB464D625DC1C4D05" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">
Length 4.7-5.0 mm. Head, pronotum and elytra with similar punctation. Prosternum carinate medially, with a prominent tooth anteromedially. Elytra slightly parallel-sided in the middle, without serial punctures laterally. Mesofemora densely pubescent, except on extreme apex. First abdominal ventrite with median carina on basal two-thirds. Fifth ventrite slightly emarginate and with a row of stout setae apically. 
<emphasis id="32A3C02BE185276E1D4A7F32FB7DF158" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Aedeagus</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="FF0ED1F4EEFA9444CD68B55BA78A426A" captionStart="Figure 6" captionStartId="F6" captionText="Figure 6. Coelostoma (Lachnocoelostoma) nankunshanense Mai &amp; Jia, sp. nov. A dorsal view B ventral view C lateral view D-F aedeagus D, E holotype D dorsal view E ventral view F aedeagus of a paratype (dorsal view). Scale bars: 1.0 mm (A-C); 0.5 mm (D-F)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1091.79564.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/666188" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">6D-F</figureCitation>
): similar to 
<taxonomicName id="DFA54C8F6D1A1CBC87647E1727BF7662" authorityName="Hebauer" authorityYear="2006" class="Insecta" family="Hydrophilidae" genus="Coelostoma" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Coelostoma turnai" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="turnai">
<emphasis id="D239B7E4A07E89BBDED5FCF183C25BE7" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="15">Coelostoma turnai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hebauer, 2006 (
<bibRefCitation id="F984881125403EE10855ADD2F354CC3A" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3887.3.4" author="Jia, F-L" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" pagination="354 - 376" refId="B13" refString="Jia, F-L, Aston, P, Fikacek, M, 2014. Review of the Chinese species of the genus Coelostoma Brulle, 1835 (Coleoptera: Hydrophilidae: Sphaeridiinae). Zootaxa 3887 (3): 354 - 376, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3887.3.4" title="Review of the Chinese species of the genus Coelostoma Brulle, 1835 (Coleoptera: Hydrophilidae: Sphaeridiinae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3887.3.4" volume="3887" year="2014">Jia et al. 2014</bibRefCitation>
: fig. 21), but median lobe wider and shorter, outer face of parameres distinctly incised subapically.
</paragraph>
<caption id="79E79EC237E450292A380642F87E3883" doi="10.3897/zookeys.1091.79564.figure6" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/666188" pageId="0" pageNumber="15" start="Figure 6" startId="F6">
